WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:16.266 --> 00:00:19.519 position:50% align:center
[sobbing]

00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:21.896 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
Ethereal...

00:00:21.980 --> 00:00:24.482 position:50% align:center
Absolutely exquisite.

00:00:24.566 --> 00:00:27.736 position:50% align:center
Power and beauty
in physical form.

00:00:27.819 --> 00:00:31.197 position:50% align:center
You are the embodiment
of all I have ever desired.

00:00:31.281 --> 00:00:33.575 position:50% align:center
[VOICE]
No! No, don't look at me!

00:00:33.658 --> 00:00:36.119 position:50% align:center
Don't look at me!

00:00:36.202 --> 00:00:37.829 position:50% align:center
I marvel at your allure.

00:00:37.912 --> 00:00:39.497 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:42.083 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
The hour of judgment is nigh.

00:00:42.167 --> 00:00:44.044 position:50% align:center
Do not deny us your grace.

00:00:44.127 --> 00:00:47.422 position:50% align:center
My salvation and humanity's
redemption rest with you.

00:00:47.505 --> 00:00:49.299 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:51.051 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
He saw the monster.

00:00:51.134 --> 00:00:53.720 position:50% align:center
And deemed me
something to be cherished.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:56.639 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
Now...

00:00:58.391 --> 00:00:59.559 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:06.816 --> 00:01:08.735 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
Leyla.

00:01:08.818 --> 00:01:13.073 position:50% align:center
Today is the day.
The day your sister returns.

00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:14.657 position:50% align:center
Hurry up and get ready.

00:01:17.535 --> 00:01:19.204 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:03.183 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
It's time for a match.

00:03:04.517 --> 00:03:07.437 position:50% align:center
The Imperial Combat Revue:
Flower Division versus

00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:09.647 position:50% align:center
Moscow Combat Revue!

00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:11.566 position:50% align:center
I'm your host, Komachi Oba!

00:03:11.649 --> 00:03:14.527 position:50% align:center
And I'm your commentator,
Reiji Shiba.

00:03:14.611 --> 00:03:17.364 position:50% align:center
The match is about
to officially kick off!

00:03:18.573 --> 00:03:20.992 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] The Moscow Combat
Revue issued a challenge

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:22.619 position:50% align:center
to the Flower Division!

00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:25.538 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Yep! Care to tell us why?

00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:28.833 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] We are not Klara M.
Ruzhkova's first revue.

00:03:28.917 --> 00:03:31.753 position:50% align:center
She is a former member of
the Moscow Combat Revue.

00:03:31.836 --> 00:03:35.382 position:50% align:center
As you know, she now belongs
to the Imperial Combat Revue:

00:03:35.465 --> 00:03:36.883 position:50% align:center
Flower Division.

00:03:36.966 --> 00:03:39.928 position:50% align:center
But the Moscow Combat Revue
wants Klara back with them!

00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.888 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Oh-ho-ho!
So, this whole match is for

00:03:41.971 --> 00:03:44.391 position:50% align:center
who gets Klara once and for all?

00:03:44.474 --> 00:03:46.935 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] That's right!
And this match is..

00:03:47.018 --> 00:03:50.146 position:50% align:center
...being held without
a single audience member!

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:54.025 position:50% align:center
Aw, man! How am I supposed
to make any money?!

00:03:54.109 --> 00:03:56.611 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] The match is,
however, being streamed

00:03:56.695 --> 00:03:58.571 position:50% align:center
for the entire world to see.

00:03:58.655 --> 00:04:00.240 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
The whole world's watching!

00:04:00.323 --> 00:04:02.534 position:50% align:center
No pressure at all!

00:04:02.617 --> 00:04:04.953 position:50% align:center
I'm pleased you
accepted our challenge.

00:04:05.036 --> 00:04:06.955 position:50% align:center
We are quite honored.

00:04:07.038 --> 00:04:09.624 position:50% align:center
An internationally
broadcast campaign?

00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:12.669 position:50% align:center
You knew we couldn't decline
without appearing weak.

00:04:12.752 --> 00:04:14.337 position:50% align:center
I am not impressed.

00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:16.423 position:50% align:center
You wound me, Commander.

00:04:16.506 --> 00:04:19.759 position:50% align:center
Still time to refuse, though
spectators wouldn't be pleased.

00:04:19.843 --> 00:04:22.762 position:50% align:center
[KANZAKI] True. Neither
would any of our allies.

00:04:22.846 --> 00:04:26.433 position:50% align:center
I'm certain every combat revue
in world is also watching.

00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:29.936 position:50% align:center
A refusal could destroy our
reputation and partnerships.

00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:31.479 position:50% align:center
You're so right.

00:04:31.563 --> 00:04:33.982 position:50% align:center
That is quite the conundrum
you've found yourselves in,

00:04:34.065 --> 00:04:38.111 position:50% align:center
isn't it? Best of luck,
Imperial Combat Revue.

00:04:38.194 --> 00:04:39.904 position:50% align:center
[KANZAKI grunts]

00:04:39.988 --> 00:04:41.406 position:50% align:center
Leyla.

00:04:41.489 --> 00:04:43.324 position:50% align:center
I leave the rest to you.

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.338 position:50% align:center
[KLARA]
I'm sorry.

00:04:56.421 --> 00:04:58.340 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Why are you apologizing?

00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:01.343 position:50% align:center
This is my fault. I'm causing
problems for you and-- Ahh!

00:05:01.426 --> 00:05:03.219 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO]
Don't be silly.

00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:05.638 position:50% align:center
They wanted a fight,
and we're giving them one.

00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50% align:center
Family takes care of each other.
Ain't that right?

00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:12.520 position:50% align:center
Now. Just cheer up!

00:05:12.604 --> 00:05:13.855 position:50% align:center
We've got this!

00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:17.067 position:50% align:center
You don't have to worry
about a thing, Klara.

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:18.401 position:50% align:center
We're here for you.

00:05:18.485 --> 00:05:21.154 position:50% align:center
And we'll protect you
no matter what!

00:05:21.237 --> 00:05:23.490 position:50% align:center
'Kay!

00:05:23.573 --> 00:05:25.158 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO chuckles]

00:05:25.241 --> 00:05:27.619 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Well!
The match is ready to begin!

00:05:27.702 --> 00:05:29.412 position:50% align:center
Let's do this thing!

00:05:29.496 --> 00:05:31.706 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] The match will
consist of three rounds total.

00:05:31.790 --> 00:05:34.042 position:50% align:center
The first round will be
a dance battle to see who can

00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:36.336 position:50% align:center
swing and sway the best!

00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:37.921 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO]
Heck yeah!

00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:40.590 position:50% align:center
If you want a dancer,
I'm your girl!

00:05:42.634 --> 00:05:44.719 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
The Flower Division is up first.

00:05:44.803 --> 00:05:48.223 position:50% align:center
Hatsuho Shinonome
is our first contender!

00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:50.684 position:50% align:center
Does our girl have the right
moves to take the win

00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:52.602 position:50% align:center
this round, folks?

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.939 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Hatsuho Shinonome!

00:06:00.777 --> 00:06:01.820 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
Okay.

00:06:01.903 --> 00:06:04.072 position:50% align:center
Let's see what
you're really capable of.

00:06:04.155 --> 00:06:06.866 position:50% align:center
This ought to be
very interesting.

00:06:06.950 --> 00:06:10.203 position:50% align:center
I know you can do this.

00:06:10.286 --> 00:06:12.455 position:50% align:center
[CLARISSA]
Hatsuho's dazzling.

00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:13.915 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Mm-hmm.

00:06:22.048 --> 00:06:25.427 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Ah! Hatsuho has
already started her routine!

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:27.929 position:50% align:center
A traditional Shinto dance!

00:06:28.013 --> 00:06:30.807 position:50% align:center
The original purpose
was to purify the body

00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:33.893 position:50% align:center
and summon a god into oneself!

00:06:33.977 --> 00:06:36.604 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Every movement
is precisely calculated!

00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:37.981 position:50% align:center
Superb!

00:06:44.029 --> 00:06:46.698 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Oh! I can see
a whole field of flowers!

00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:48.450 position:50% align:center
Those are special
projected images!

00:06:48.533 --> 00:06:50.076 position:50% align:center
What amazing technology!

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:53.246 position:50% align:center
Who on Earth could've
made such a thing, huh?

00:06:53.329 --> 00:06:54.372 position:50% align:center
It was none other than--

00:06:54.456 --> 00:06:56.791 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
It's time turn up the heat!

00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:23.777 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.904 position:50% align:center
[applause]

00:07:31.701 --> 00:07:34.579 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA] Beautiful cherry
blossoms of the East.

00:07:34.662 --> 00:07:37.791 position:50% align:center
Well... Kaminski is watching.

00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:41.294 position:50% align:center
I will die before
I disappoint him.

00:07:41.378 --> 00:07:43.254 position:50% align:center
She set the bar pretty high.

00:07:43.338 --> 00:07:45.882 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR] Indeed.
But it just won't be enough.

00:07:47.509 --> 00:07:48.927 position:50% align:center
I have returned!

00:07:49.010 --> 00:07:52.222 position:50% align:center
You were amazing!
I'm so proud of you, Hatsuho!

00:07:52.305 --> 00:07:55.892 position:50% align:center
Aw. Way to make
a gal blush, Sakura.

00:07:55.975 --> 00:07:57.644 position:50% align:center
You were like a magical fairy!

00:07:57.727 --> 00:08:00.188 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO chuckles]
Thanks, munchkin!

00:08:00.271 --> 00:08:02.023 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Time to cool off!

00:08:02.107 --> 00:08:05.026 position:50% align:center
Up next from the Moscow Combat
Revue is the girl cloaked

00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:07.904 position:50% align:center
in a veil of snow
and ice that slays!

00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:09.322 position:50% align:center
Leyla!

00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:13.785 position:50% align:center
Now. Show them how it's done.

00:08:13.868 --> 00:08:16.329 position:50% align:center
Let them witness true beauty.

00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:25.296 position:50% align:center
[REIJI]
Splendid!

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:26.506 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Huh? What is?

00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:27.882 position:50% align:center
It's The Black Swan!

00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:30.468 position:50% align:center
This is a dance best known
as a pas de deux,

00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:32.095 position:50% align:center
which is meant to be
performed with a partner

00:08:32.178 --> 00:08:34.264 position:50% align:center
and she's doing it
perfectly alone!

00:08:34.347 --> 00:08:35.974 position:50% align:center
Uh, sure.

00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:44.607 position:50% align:center
She moves almost
like she's flying.

00:08:44.691 --> 00:08:46.818 position:50% align:center
There's more than that.

00:08:46.901 --> 00:08:49.738 position:50% align:center
She's crying with no one there.

00:08:49.821 --> 00:08:51.531 position:50% align:center
It's her sorrow.

00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:03.126 position:50% align:center
This stirs emotions.

00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:05.879 position:50% align:center
It's far more
compelling than ours.

00:09:13.845 --> 00:09:15.138 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA panting]

00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:18.058 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] That was something
else, ladies and gents!

00:09:18.141 --> 00:09:21.603 position:50% align:center
And so ends the first round
of our combat revue match!

00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:23.646 position:50% align:center
[REIJI]
Truly an elegant Black Swan!

00:09:23.730 --> 00:09:25.940 position:50% align:center
32 fouettÃ©s is not an easy feat!

00:09:26.024 --> 00:09:27.150 position:50% align:center
I can't say who did better!

00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:28.651 position:50% align:center
I'm feeling a lot
of feelings right now

00:09:28.735 --> 00:09:30.945 position:50% align:center
and I don't know
how feel about that!

00:09:31.029 --> 00:09:33.948 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that makes
two of us, Shiba!

00:09:34.032 --> 00:09:36.284 position:50% align:center
Here come the scores!

00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:38.787 position:50% align:center
[REIJI]
First, for technical!

00:09:38.870 --> 00:09:40.538 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Matching scores!

00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:42.582 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO growls]
Seriously?

00:09:42.665 --> 00:09:44.584 position:50% align:center
You're dead even...

00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:48.088 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Next up is artistic impression!

00:09:48.171 --> 00:09:51.758 position:50% align:center
Ah! Moscow got a perfect score!

00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:54.302 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] Artistic impression
determines the winner!

00:09:54.386 --> 00:09:57.597 position:50% align:center
Ah. I thought the scores
would be more of a nail-biter.

00:09:57.681 --> 00:09:59.683 position:50% align:center
The judges are
old-fashioned European.

00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:03.311 position:50% align:center
Evidently, they chose to favor
the dance they knew best.

00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:04.813 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:04.896 --> 00:10:08.775 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] The Moscow Combat
Revue wins the first round!

00:10:08.858 --> 00:10:11.027 position:50% align:center
Klara, I'm so sorry...

00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:12.570 position:50% align:center
[KLARA]
Mm. Don't be.

00:10:12.654 --> 00:10:15.073 position:50% align:center
Your dance was
wonderful, Hatsuho!

00:10:15.156 --> 00:10:17.575 position:50% align:center
We can make up the difference.

00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:20.120 position:50% align:center
Hey, she's right.
We're still in!

00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:22.539 position:50% align:center
Let's kick butt
for Klara, ladies!

00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:23.998 position:50% align:center
[IMPERIAL REVUE]
Right!

00:10:28.253 --> 00:10:29.629 position:50% align:center
Kaminski!

00:10:31.047 --> 00:10:34.467 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
Leyla. You did very well.

00:10:34.551 --> 00:10:35.468 position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:10:35.552 --> 00:10:37.512 position:50% align:center
Now prepare for what's ahead.

00:10:41.808 --> 00:10:43.435 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
Of course.

00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:46.646 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Up next!

00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:49.607 position:50% align:center
For the second round, please
welcome the best and only ninja

00:10:49.691 --> 00:10:52.610 position:50% align:center
I know-- Azami Mochizuki!

00:10:52.694 --> 00:10:55.488 position:50% align:center
Will she be prepared for...

00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:02.537 position:50% align:center
...a bread-eating obstacle
course scavenger hunt

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:05.165 position:50% align:center
we're calling The Hattori?

00:11:05.248 --> 00:11:08.293 position:50% align:center
This intricate circuit is like
no other out there, folks!

00:11:08.376 --> 00:11:10.253 position:50% align:center
And I should know because
I'm the one that came up with

00:11:10.337 --> 00:11:12.047 position:50% align:center
the whole thing!

00:11:13.590 --> 00:11:15.717 position:50% align:center
We know who's playing
for Flower Division.

00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.303 position:50% align:center
From Moscow's team is...

00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:19.596 position:50% align:center
Uh!

00:11:19.679 --> 00:11:21.431 position:50% align:center
Nobody?!

00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:23.600 position:50% align:center
What's the big deal, huh?!

00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:28.521 position:50% align:center
Understand, my revue
is one of dignity.

00:11:28.605 --> 00:11:32.233 position:50% align:center
Far too refined to participate
in something so uncouth.

00:11:32.317 --> 00:11:35.862 position:50% align:center
Thus, Moscow is obligated
to withdraw from this.

00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:37.572 position:50% align:center
A withdraw...?

00:11:37.655 --> 00:11:41.659 position:50% align:center
You heard him. The Moscow Combat
Revue chooses to forfeit!

00:11:41.743 --> 00:11:44.954 position:50% align:center
Who am I to deprive the Flower
Division of at least one win?

00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:46.998 position:50% align:center
I'm not without
empathy after all.

00:11:47.082 --> 00:11:49.209 position:50% align:center
Please consider it a gift.

00:11:49.292 --> 00:11:51.836 position:50% align:center
He's attempting to mock us.

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:56.675 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] The 2nd round goes
to the Imperial Combat Revue!

00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:58.218 position:50% align:center
I won!

00:11:58.301 --> 00:12:00.261 position:50% align:center
You won by default, Azami.

00:12:00.345 --> 00:12:02.097 position:50% align:center
But, a win is still a win.

00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.641 position:50% align:center
Which means the last round
is a tie-breaker!

00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:06.518 position:50% align:center
It's going to be mock combat!

00:12:06.601 --> 00:12:08.937 position:50% align:center
We're gonna win.
Am I right, girls?

00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:10.772 position:50% align:center
[IMPERIAL REVUE]
Right!

00:12:12.774 --> 00:12:14.609 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
Is this what you want?

00:12:14.693 --> 00:12:18.405 position:50% align:center
A forfeit doesn't necessarily
give off the right impression.

00:12:18.488 --> 00:12:22.617 position:50% align:center
Heh. Let them wonder.

00:12:22.701 --> 00:12:25.453 position:50% align:center
The curtain is about to rise.

00:12:25.537 --> 00:12:29.874 position:50% align:center
This final contest is our chance
to divulge their looming fate.

00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:32.502 position:50% align:center
No more hiding
my ambitions, Leyla.

00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:36.923 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:47.559 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Here it is!

00:12:47.642 --> 00:12:49.436 position:50% align:center
The end of the match
between the Flower Division

00:12:49.519 --> 00:12:51.438 position:50% align:center
and the Moscow Combat Revue!

00:12:51.521 --> 00:12:55.567 position:50% align:center
Our last round
will be a mock combat!

00:12:55.650 --> 00:12:57.402 position:50% align:center
A huge tower
and walls have

00:12:57.485 --> 00:13:00.155 position:50% align:center
just finished materializing!

00:13:02.407 --> 00:13:04.242 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] And...
both of our teams have

00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:06.036 position:50% align:center
entered the battlefield!

00:13:07.829 --> 00:13:10.623 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] Each revue has
three units for this round.

00:13:10.707 --> 00:13:13.335 position:50% align:center
The official winner is
the first one to rescue Klara

00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:15.420 position:50% align:center
from the tower she's trapped in!

00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:18.089 position:50% align:center
For safety's sake, both teams
are banned from using

00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:19.549 position:50% align:center
long-range weapons.

00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:21.843 position:50% align:center
Only practice
blades are allowed!

00:13:24.054 --> 00:13:25.347 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
All right, everyone.

00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:27.599 position:50% align:center
Get her out of there
as fast as possible!

00:13:27.682 --> 00:13:30.643 position:50% align:center
Yeah! I'm not gonna
let that kid down!

00:13:30.727 --> 00:13:32.103 position:50% align:center
Me, either.

00:13:34.022 --> 00:13:35.565 position:50% align:center
[KAORU] We don't
have any detailed data on

00:13:35.648 --> 00:13:38.526 position:50% align:center
this new Moscow Combat Revue,
but based on what

00:13:38.610 --> 00:13:40.528 position:50% align:center
we've previously
seen from them,

00:13:40.612 --> 00:13:42.947 position:50% align:center
they're quite proficient
as an overall team.

00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:47.035 position:50% align:center
We're more skilled with blades.
We have the advantage here.

00:13:47.118 --> 00:13:49.079 position:50% align:center
Flower Division can win this.

00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:50.622 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:13:50.705 --> 00:13:52.332 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Both teams are prepared!

00:13:52.415 --> 00:13:54.959 position:50% align:center
It all ends here,
ladies and gentlemen!

00:13:57.212 --> 00:13:58.463 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA grunts]

00:14:01.091 --> 00:14:02.592 position:50% align:center
It's time.

00:14:02.676 --> 00:14:06.054 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Ach! Ready, set, and go!

00:14:09.099 --> 00:14:12.310 position:50% align:center
[HATSUHO] Out of our way!
Flower Division coming through!

00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:17.565 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI] Looks like Moscow
is making a play!

00:14:17.649 --> 00:14:20.568 position:50% align:center
That's strange. Their leader
isn't moving at all.

00:14:20.652 --> 00:14:22.404 position:50% align:center
Ah?! You're right!

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:25.407 position:50% align:center
Leyla hasn't budged
from her start position.

00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:27.617 position:50% align:center
[CLARISSA] Hatsuho has moved
down the central passageway

00:14:27.701 --> 00:14:29.160 position:50% align:center
to block it.

00:14:30.537 --> 00:14:31.705 position:50% align:center
[ANASTASIA]
And while she defends,

00:14:31.788 --> 00:14:33.248 position:50% align:center
Sakura's scaling the tower!

00:14:33.331 --> 00:14:34.708 position:50% align:center
[CLARISSA]
Yes!

00:14:36.543 --> 00:14:38.920 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:45.927 position:50% align:center
[CLARISSA]
Azami's providing Sakura cover!

00:14:46.011 --> 00:14:47.178 position:50% align:center
[AZAMI]
Hah!

00:14:50.348 --> 00:14:51.891 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
Oh! You hate to see it!

00:14:51.975 --> 00:14:54.686 position:50% align:center
Is one of Moscow's
units down already?

00:14:54.769 --> 00:14:57.188 position:50% align:center
The Flower Division
is taking no prisoners!

00:14:57.272 --> 00:14:58.732 position:50% align:center
[REIJI]
Sakura's reaching the top!

00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:01.735 position:50% align:center
Are we about to see
this thing end so soon?

00:15:01.818 --> 00:15:03.028 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:15:03.111 --> 00:15:05.405 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Klara, I'm almost there!

00:15:06.156 --> 00:15:07.532 position:50% align:center
This doesn't sit right.

00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:10.076 position:50% align:center
Ah! What's that?

00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:17.125 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Klara!

00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:18.126 position:50% align:center
[KLARA]
Sakura!

00:15:18.209 --> 00:15:19.627 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA grunts]

00:15:25.133 --> 00:15:26.593 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA gasps]

00:15:30.138 --> 00:15:31.264 position:50% align:center
[yelps]

00:15:31.348 --> 00:15:32.682 position:50% align:center
Sakura!

00:15:32.766 --> 00:15:36.394 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA grunts]
Where did they come from?

00:15:39.856 --> 00:15:41.399 position:50% align:center
[AZAMI]
Leave this one to me!

00:15:41.483 --> 00:15:42.984 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Thanks, Azami!

00:15:43.068 --> 00:15:46.363 position:50% align:center
What's going on?
There are other Moscow units?

00:15:46.446 --> 00:15:49.491 position:50% align:center
Yes. The ones Hatsuho
and Azami took down

00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:51.826 position:50% align:center
are lying beneath the tower.

00:15:51.910 --> 00:15:54.371 position:50% align:center
Something is wrong here.

00:15:56.581 --> 00:16:00.043 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI]
Hmph. Leyla.

00:16:00.126 --> 00:16:03.755 position:50% align:center
Time for the bell
to start ringing.

00:16:03.838 --> 00:16:06.800 position:50% align:center
It will be done.

00:16:06.883 --> 00:16:09.969 position:50% align:center
The hour of judgment is here!

00:16:11.638 --> 00:16:13.390 position:50% align:center
[KLARA gasps]

00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:17.602 position:50% align:center
Stop it!

00:16:17.686 --> 00:16:19.062 position:50% align:center
Klara!

00:16:24.651 --> 00:16:25.694 position:50% align:center
What the heck?!

00:16:25.777 --> 00:16:27.362 position:50% align:center
All the power has gone out!

00:16:27.445 --> 00:16:30.115 position:50% align:center
Does that mean
the feed's gone dead, too?

00:16:30.198 --> 00:16:31.116 position:50% align:center
Come on!

00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:32.117 position:50% align:center
Was there an outage?

00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:33.243 position:50% align:center
[CROWD MAN 8C]
A glitch?

00:16:33.326 --> 00:16:34.786 position:50% align:center
What is happening?

00:16:39.874 --> 00:16:41.126 position:50% align:center
Fishy.

00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:43.086 position:50% align:center
Something here stinks.

00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:45.630 position:50% align:center
Arise.

00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.895 position:50% align:center
Sakura, run!

00:17:00.979 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA gasps]

00:17:07.652 --> 00:17:09.320 position:50% align:center
They're using real weapons!

00:17:09.404 --> 00:17:10.321 position:50% align:center
Oh no!

00:17:10.405 --> 00:17:12.532 position:50% align:center
--Azami!
--[AZAMI] I'm on it!

00:17:14.367 --> 00:17:15.785 position:50% align:center
So long.

00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:17.704 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:17.787 --> 00:17:18.872 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:17:18.955 --> 00:17:20.331 position:50% align:center
Azami!

00:17:20.415 --> 00:17:22.375 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:28.965 position:50% align:center
Damn it!

00:17:30.467 --> 00:17:32.135 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Why are you doing this?

00:17:32.218 --> 00:17:34.596 position:50% align:center
And with ammunition?

00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:37.432 position:50% align:center
Leyla. You know
this isn't the way!

00:17:37.515 --> 00:17:41.102 position:50% align:center
But it is. Everything is
as Kaminski wills it.

00:17:42.979 --> 00:17:45.273 position:50% align:center
We have back up, but not a lot.

00:17:45.357 --> 00:17:47.734 position:50% align:center
Kaminski, what is
the meaning of this?!

00:17:47.817 --> 00:17:50.070 position:50% align:center
Call your people off
this second!

00:17:50.153 --> 00:17:53.907 position:50% align:center
Claris, Anastasia!
Go get Kaminski! Hurry!

00:17:55.784 --> 00:17:56.868 position:50% align:center
Hands up!

00:17:56.951 --> 00:18:00.080 position:50% align:center
Kaminski, put a stop
to this immediately!

00:18:02.415 --> 00:18:04.584 position:50% align:center
[BOTH] No way.
It's the Black Cape!

00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:10.048 position:50% align:center
[REIJI] Crap, crap, crap, crap!
What do I do?!

00:18:10.131 --> 00:18:11.883 position:50% align:center
[KOMACHI]
I still can't see anything!

00:18:11.966 --> 00:18:13.343 position:50% align:center
What happened?!

00:18:13.426 --> 00:18:14.511 position:50% align:center
[REIJI]
Damn!

00:18:14.594 --> 00:18:16.429 position:50% align:center
All the lines have
been totally severed!

00:18:16.513 --> 00:18:18.223 position:50% align:center
Think, you beautiful bastard!

00:18:18.306 --> 00:18:21.851 position:50% align:center
Ah. Yeah, that might be just
what I need, let's see here...

00:18:21.935 --> 00:18:24.270 position:50% align:center
My baby! This could work!

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:30.527 position:50% align:center
[LANCELOT gasps]
It's back!

00:18:30.610 --> 00:18:32.195 position:50% align:center
[ARTHUR]
What is this...?

00:18:33.738 --> 00:18:35.740 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
I'm taking Klara!

00:18:35.824 --> 00:18:36.908 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
No, you're not!

00:18:38.743 --> 00:18:40.120 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Please, listen to me--

00:18:40.203 --> 00:18:41.246 position:50% align:center
[gasps, grunts]

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:44.249 position:50% align:center
Sakura!

00:18:44.332 --> 00:18:46.960 position:50% align:center
I am not letting you
take Klara away from us!

00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:49.045 position:50% align:center
You are not getting past me!

00:18:52.382 --> 00:18:56.970 position:50% align:center
Sakura, please stop!
Just go and forget about me!

00:18:58.972 --> 00:19:00.640 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
I can't.

00:19:00.724 --> 00:19:01.683 position:50% align:center
I won't.

00:19:01.766 --> 00:19:03.476 position:50% align:center
Listen, Klara.

00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:06.438 position:50% align:center
Family doesn't
give up or forget!

00:19:06.521 --> 00:19:07.605 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:21.369 --> 00:19:23.997 position:50% align:center
[sobbing]
Sakura...

00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:28.585 position:50% align:center
Heh! You think you're family...?

00:19:28.668 --> 00:19:30.962 position:50% align:center
Ridiculous!

00:19:31.046 --> 00:19:33.840 position:50% align:center
You're not even related!

00:19:33.923 --> 00:19:35.884 position:50% align:center
Maybe not by blood.

00:19:35.967 --> 00:19:37.635 position:50% align:center
But we're family
where it counts!

00:19:37.719 --> 00:19:39.095 position:50% align:center
No, you're not!

00:19:41.056 --> 00:19:43.016 position:50% align:center
[shrieks]

00:19:43.099 --> 00:19:44.642 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
Remember, Klara!

00:19:44.726 --> 00:19:46.353 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:19:46.436 --> 00:19:48.563 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA] Remember who
your real family is!

00:19:48.646 --> 00:19:50.065 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:53.318 --> 00:19:55.153 position:50% align:center
Remember, sister!

00:19:57.822 --> 00:19:59.657 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:19:59.741 --> 00:20:02.619 position:50% align:center
You have to remember, Klara.

00:20:02.702 --> 00:20:05.497 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Sestra.

00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:06.748 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA]
Move.

00:20:06.831 --> 00:20:08.291 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA screams]

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:09.584 position:50% align:center
Sakura!

00:20:11.961 --> 00:20:12.879 position:50% align:center
Come home, Klara.

00:20:12.962 --> 00:20:13.880 position:50% align:center
No!

00:20:13.963 --> 00:20:15.757 position:50% align:center
Just stop it! Ah!

00:20:17.217 --> 00:20:19.803 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:20:19.886 --> 00:20:22.639 position:50% align:center
Klara!

00:20:22.722 --> 00:20:27.894 position:50% align:center
No more!

00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:30.230 position:50% align:center
[LEYLA grunts]
Klara!

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:35.902 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI laughs]

00:20:35.985 --> 00:20:38.446 position:50% align:center
Look who has finally awoken!

00:20:38.530 --> 00:20:41.241 position:50% align:center
Klara!

00:20:41.324 --> 00:20:45.328 position:50% align:center
Now, Messenger of God, Klara.

00:20:45.412 --> 00:20:48.873 position:50% align:center
The hour of
judgment has arrived!

00:20:48.957 --> 00:20:51.626 position:50% align:center
[KAMINSKI] The one who
buries all with flames!

00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:54.087 position:50% align:center
One who will create a new world!

00:20:54.170 --> 00:20:56.631 position:50% align:center
The savior!

00:20:56.715 --> 00:20:58.550 position:50% align:center
Manifest, Klara!

00:20:58.633 --> 00:21:02.053 position:50% align:center
Bring forth a new,
rightly just world!

00:21:02.137 --> 00:21:04.764 position:50% align:center
Fulfill your destiny!

00:21:22.073 --> 00:21:24.826 position:50% align:center
[KLARA sobbing]

00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:32.125 position:50% align:center
Klara...

00:21:35.420 --> 00:21:37.005 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:40.467 --> 00:21:42.302 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Wait! Klara!

00:21:45.096 --> 00:21:48.641 position:50% align:center
Klara!

00:23:23.862 --> 00:23:27.115 position:50% align:center
[KAMIYAMA] As disaster
rocked Tokyo, I was elsewhere.

00:23:27.198 --> 00:23:29.367 position:50% align:center
Though my team needs me,
I have to know the truth

00:23:29.451 --> 00:23:31.786 position:50% align:center
behind the incident
that started it all.

00:23:31.870 --> 00:23:34.205 position:50% align:center
What secrets will I
uncover in Russia?

00:23:34.289 --> 00:23:36.041 position:50% align:center
Will it make a difference?

00:23:36.124 --> 00:23:39.252 position:50% align:center
Next time on Sakura Wars
the Animation, Episode 9:

00:23:39.336 --> 00:23:41.921 position:50% align:center
"Unbelievable!
The Truth About Klara!"

00:23:42.005 --> 00:23:45.717 position:50% align:center
The winds of adventure blow over
the Taisho cherry blossoms!